  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\nThe expected `TransactionFailed` error in here in `test_vmc_handler.py` is not caused by expected case.\r\n```python\r\n# if a header is added before its parent header is added, `add_header` should fail\r\n    # TransactionFailed raised when assertions fail\r\n    with pytest.raises(TransactionFailed):\r\n        header_parent_not_added = mk_testing_colhdr(\r\n            vmc,\r\n            shard_id,\r\n            header0_1.hash,\r\n            1,\r\n        )\r\n        add_header_constant_call(vmc, header_parent_not_added)\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter some debugging, it turns out that this error is caused by wrong period number provided, instead of the expected cause(`if a header is added before its parent header is added, `add_header` should fail`).\r\nCause: Since a local function call(i.e., no real transaction broadcasted) in web3.py will use the latest mined block number as `block.number`, this cause the `addHeader` to fetch the wrong block hash with the lates mined block number(should be latest mined block number+1) and results in assertion failure in contract.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nCheck if we can customize environment parameters(block number) in web3.py or come up with different cases that would have the expected result(`if a header is added before its parent header is added, `add_header` should fail`).",
